<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAGS">
    <summary>
      <para>Flags for indicating a subset of components used with video decode histogram. This enumeration is used by the <see cref="D3D12_FEATURE_DATA_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM" /> structure.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAG_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>No associated component.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAG_Y">
    <summary>
      <para>If the format is a YUV format, indicates the Y component.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAG_U">
    <summary>
      <para>If the format is a YUV format, indicates the U component.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAG_V">
    <summary>
      <para>If the format is a YUV format, indicates the V component.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAG_R">
    <summary>
      <para>If the format is an RGB/BGR format, indicates the R component.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAG_G">
    <summary>
      <para>If the format is an RGB/BGR format, indicates the G component.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAG_B">
    <summary>
      <para>If the format is an RGB/BGR format, indicates the B component.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_DECODE_HISTOGRAM_COMPONENT_FLAG_A">
    <summary>
      <para>If the format is an RGB/BGR format, indicates the A component.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>